RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. (PLUS UP TO $6,600 Open ATB) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 119 lbs. (Texas Thoroughbred Association Futurity Eligible Preferred).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MILLIE G vied for the lead under a steady hand ride, then gained command heading into the turn, and held on well to prove best. CLEARLY COPPER stalked the pace while two wide, was well rated along the inside of the bend, angled out two wide in the early stretch, then dug in to close fast for a gamely second. GYPSAN chased the pace while three wide, was urging on the turn, then rallied mid stretch to close well. SPEAK SOFTLY vied for the lead from the inside under a gamely drive then gave way in late stretch. CHAINSAW CITY settled along the inside, then bid on the turn and into the lane but it was too little too late. THAROLITE was off slowly then chased the pace from the inside, rallied on the turn then flattened out in the final sixteenth. NATURAL TOUCH was under a hard drive while stalking the pace while four wide into the turn, then flattened out in the stretch. KOLLYNS JULIE bid for the lead early, then settle in the two path behind the field and faded throughout and was no rally.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. (PLUS UP TO $1,650 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. RACE.FOOTNOTES: MUD ON MY BOOTS sped to a clear advantage shortly from the gate, set a well rated pace maintaining his margin to mid-stretch, weakened coming to the wire but just held on in a blanket finish. TIZ BODHI BOY taken off the pace and allowed to settle into stride down the backside, cut the corner turning for home and closed with a rush up the fence to just miss. TEXAN FARMER prompted the pace while well placed throughout, drifted wide in the lane while steadily gaining on the pacesetter and surged in last few strides in a good effort. MR. VALENTINO rated in mid-pack and found his best stride late to make a belated rally to hit the board. LAST FLASHY showed speed for a half mile to press the pace and tired down the lane. GOLD CAPO broke alertly, immediately dropped to the back of the field and was never a factor. BINDING HEART well placed along the rail just tracking the early pace for a half mile and weakened coming home.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: TATANKA sped to the lead immediately from the gate, opened a wide advantage for the first run down the lane, was well rated while maintaining a clear lead down the backside, responded when engaged by several approaching the final bend, drew clear again and held the late closer safe. KAZAN (IRE) rated near the rear of the field through the first two turns from between horses, gained ground into the far turn to be in striking distance of the leader while angling out for the drive and closed well to be second best. JOHAN ZOFFANI (IRE) stalked the distant pacesetter from the rail through the turns and down the backside, moved to engage the pacesetter entering the far turn for the second time, threatened briefly but could not sustain the bid and finished evenly to hold the show. SEDUCTIVE U S A raced three wide in the second flight through each turn, moved boldly down the backside to challenge for the lead from four wide and flattened out turning for home. MOOJAB JR slow early to trail the field for the first mile and rallied passed tired rivals in the stretch while never threatening. MIDAS CAT tracked the leader from the fence down the backside, made a brief bid and gave out turning for home. GOSPEL MUSKETEER stalked the leaders for the first five-eighths of a mile and came up empty.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 9 7 1/2F Turf CR: 79. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. (PLUS UP TO $6,600 Open ATB) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For $20,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts). (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this rac e over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile. If the race is for two year olds, it will be run at Seven Furlongs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIAMI MOONLIGHT saved ground throughout the first three quarters along the inside, then angled out five wide in the early stretch to surge down the lane, dropped in deep stretch and was up at the wire to prevail. SPIN TO WIN was bumped at the start, then was well rated along the inside while tracking the pace down the backstretch, then bid on the far turn to rally in the early stretch and was closing willingly just missing success in the end. DAWSON CITY was bumped at the start, then tracked the pace from the two path, bid on the far turn and into the early stretch while four wide, rallied gamely then checked in deep stretch and was best for show in the end. CITY NIGHTS vied for the lead between rivals, was in a hard drive throughout the far turn, then gave way in the stretch. MOHAYMEN HOLIDAY raced in the middle of the field while three wide, made a mild bid on the far turn then closed well from the five path down the stretch but it wasn't enough. KERAUNOS settled in the two path, then bid from the inside on the far turn, came out four wide in the early stretch and was closing well but it wasn't enough. IT'LL DO vied for the lead from the inside, was in a long drive leaving the far turn then tired in late stretch. FREEPORT was in a strong drive to vie for the lead while three wide, was used up on the far turn, then weakened in the stretch. There was a STEWARD'S INQUIRY in regards to interference in the stretch drive. After reviewing the replay, no change was made to the order of finish.
